The PR introduces exactly one new call site: `onClick={() => openQuickAdd()}`. Since `openQuickAdd` is a synchronous Zustand setter (`set({ quickAddOpen: true })`), it cannot throw — no error handling is needed or appropriate there.

Three pre-existing error handlers in `Sidebar.tsx` are present in the diff's context but were not modified:
- Two `localStorage` try/catch blocks with intentional silent fallbacks (correct for storage quota/private mode scenarios)
- One `handleQuickAddSubmit` try/catch that correctly sets user-visible error state and uses `finally` for cleanup

All patterns are consistent with the rest of the codebase (`CommandPalette.tsx`, `useKeyboardShortcuts.ts` both call `openQuickAdd()` the same way without wrapping). Findings written to the artifact.
